-----------------------------------------------------------------------	
	JS Auto Validate
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

You must define the validation rules in a HTML file. It`s very simple and fast.

Actualy the file "default.js" you can create two basic types of validation rules:

	Not Null and E-mail 
	
	
Add the file "default.js" in project and define a rule <input type="text" in property ACCEPT.


Properties of tag INPUT :

	ACCEPT receive the type of validation
	
	TITLE receive the name for input


DIV to display error message :

	<div id="Errors"></div>


Example :

	- Its input required NotNull and Email
		<input type="text" name="username" title="Username" accept="notnull,email" />
	
	- Its input required only Email
		<input type="text" name="email" title="Username" accept="email" />
	
	- Its input required only NotNull
		<input type="text" name="username" title="Username" accept="notnull" />
	
	